        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Who is Blue Platypus for on the company side?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">Companies in the $10M–$200M ARR range that need senior fractional leadership — CMO, CFO, COO, CRO — but aren't ready for, or don't need, a full-time hire. If you have a real problem and a real budget, we can find you someone who's solved it before.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Who is Blue Platypus for on the executive side?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">Experienced operators who are doing fractional work — or want to — and are tired of competing on LinkedIn clout. If your work speaks for itself, we built this for you.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">I've tried fractional hires before and it didn't work. Why would this be different?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">Usually fractional fails for one of three reasons: wrong scope, wrong fit, or wrong expectations on both sides. Our process is built to surface all three before anyone signs anything. The Fractional Fit Score exists specifically to prevent the expensive mismatch.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How is this different from just posting on LinkedIn or using a staffing firm?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">LinkedIn favors visibility, not capability. Staffing firms optimize for placement speed and margin. We optimize for match quality — which means we'll tell you when it's not the right fit instead of filling a seat to close a deal.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does it cost?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">Pricing is structured for both sides of the market. Reach out to discuss what's right for your situation — we don't believe in one-size-fits-all engagement models any more than we believe in one-size-fits-all hires.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How quickly can I expect a match?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">We don't rush matches. A fast bad match costs everyone more than a slightly slower right one. That said, our active talent pool means most companies see qualified options within two weeks of onboarding.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What if the match doesn't work out?<svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-a">We stay involved. This isn't a handoff-and-goodbye model. If something isn't working — scope creep, misaligned expectations, a change in company direction — we're in the room to help course-correct or rematch.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:2.5rem; background:var(--white); border-radius:var(--radius); border:1px solid var(--gray-100); box-shadow:var(--shadow); padding:1.8rem; text-align:center">
        <p style="color:var(--gray-500); margin-bottom:1rem">Still have questions?</p>
        <a href="mailto:evolve@blueplatypus.online" class="btn-primary">Email evolve@blueplatypus.online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  function showPage(name) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.page').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
    document.getElementById('page-' + name).classList.add('active');
    window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
    if (name !== 'register') resetRegister();
  }

  const origRegisterHTML = document.getElementById('register-form-wrap').innerHTML;
  function resetRegister() {
    document.getElementById('register-form-wrap').innerHTML = origRegisterHTML;
  }

  function handleRegister(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const first = document.getElementById('r-first').value;
    const role  = document.getElementById('r-role');
    const roleLabel = role.options[role.selectedIndex].text;
    document.getElementById('register-form-wrap').innerHTML = `
      <div class="success-box">
        <div class="success-icon">
          <svg width="34" height="34" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>You're in, ${first}!</h3>
        <p>Your intake as <strong>${roleLabel}</strong> has been submitted. A member of the Blue Platypus team will reach out within one business day.<br><br>In the meantime, complete the full assessment below.</p>
        <a href="https://forms.gle/cK2jcDrn5QS32JUp7r" target="_blank" class="btn-primary" style="margin-bottom:.8rem;display:inline-block">Take the Full Assessment →</a><br>
        <a href="#" style="color:var(--teal-dark);font-size:.9rem" onclick="showPage('home'); return false;">← Back to Home</a>
      </div>`;
  }

  function toggleFaq(btn) {
    const answer = btn.nextElementSibling;
    const isOpen = answer.classList.contains('open');
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-a').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('open'));
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-q').forEach(q => q.classList.remove('open'));
    if (!isOpen) { answer.classList.add('open'); btn.classList.add('open'); }
  }
</script>
</body>
</html>
